The paper deals with visual place recognition in the robotics domain, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of hashing and quantization techniques, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper presents a novel approach for achieving high recall rates with low storage and computational requirements, which could be of interest to researchers in the systems and control (cs.SD) sub-category.
